
## Navigating web pages
Navigating the web is all about hyper text as well as hyperlinking in HTML.

Hypertext in HTML
Hypertext is created using the <a> tag in combination with the href="url" attribute, where URL is the address or location users are redirected to, usually to another web page.

#Navigating and Hyperlinking 
A navigation system is a section of a graphical user interface intended to aid visitors in accessing information. Navigation uses hyperlinking to allow users to navigate between web pages.

Navigation and hyperlinking
<nav>
    <ul>
       <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
       <li><a href="#">Learn Code</a></li> 
       <li><a href="#">Register</a></li>
    </ul>
</nav>

*The <nav> tag defines a set of navigation links.
*Often used with an unordered list <ul> and href attribute.

-->Navigating Web Pages in HTML
Navigation in HTML means moving from:
1.one page to another
2.one section to another
3.an external website using links.

Navigation is mainly done using the <a> (anchor) tag.
ğŸ”— Basic Page Navigation

1. Navigate to another web page
<a href="about.html">About Us</a>
â¡ï¸ Opens about.html

2. Navigate to another website
<a href="https://www.google.com">Google</a>

3. Open link in a new tab
<a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Google</a>

#Internal Page Navigation (Same Page)
Used to jump to a section on the same page.

<a href="#contact">Go to Contact</a>

<h2 id="contact">Contact Us</h2>
âœ” #id is used
âœ” Common in long pages

ğŸ“ Navigation Between Folders
<a href="pages/login.html">Login</a>
<a href="../index.html">Home</a>

../ â†’ one folder back

/ â†’ root directory

ğŸ§­ Navigation Menu Example
