##Adding comments in HTML
A comment is a descriptive text added to the HTML document that does not render in the browser.
*Used to insert comments in source code.
*Enables developers to explain code.
*To include comments in source code use the following notation.
	<!---comment here-->
e.g., 
<nav>
    <ul>
      <!--This is a navigation system with 4 hyperlinks-->
       <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
       <li><a href="#">Learn Code</a></li> 
       <li><a href="#">Excercises</a></li>
       <li><a href="#">Register</a></li>
    </ul>
</nav>


##HTML Attribute
An HTML attribute gives extra information about an HTML element.
Attributes are written inside the opening tag and usually come in name="value" format.

ğŸ§ª Basic Syntax
<tagname attribute="value">Content</tagname>


Example:

<a href="https://www.google.com">Google</a>
Here:
href â†’ attribute
"https://www.google.com" â†’ value

â­ Common HTML Attributes
1. href
Used in links.
<a href="about.html">About</a>

2. src
Used for images, videos.
<img src="image.jpg">

3. alt
Alternate text for images.
<img src="logo.png" alt="Company Logo">

4. id
Gives a unique identity.
<p id="para1">Hello</p>

5. class
Used to group elements (CSS).
<p class="text">Welcome</p>

6. style
Inline CSS styling.
<p style="color:red;">Red text</p>

7. title
Tooltip text on hover.
<p title="This is a paragraph">Hover me</p>

8. target
Where to open link.
<a href="https://google.com" target="_blank">Google</a>

9. disabled
Disable input or button.
<button disabled>Submit</button>

10. placeholder
Hint inside input box.
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter name">

ğŸ§  Types of HTML Attributes
ğŸ”¹ 1. Global Attributes (work with any tag)
id
class
style
title
hidden

ğŸ”¹ 2. Specific Attributes (work with some tags)
href â†’ <a>
src â†’ <img>
type â†’ <input>
value â†’ <input>
